92 IMMORTAL LIST~
`@i`$MM `$L`@i`$ST`@:``

Extra bits 
Weapon affects (v4)
Wear bits 
Weapon type (v0)
Weapon noun (v3)
Average Damage (v1) (v2)
Item Affects Table
~

93 AVERAGE DAMAGE V1 V2~
`$AVERAGE DAMAGE`@:``
  V1 and V2 determine the avg dam.

  Command: set obj <obj> v? <number>
  Example: set obj holy v1 5
           set obj holy v2 6

 The holy avenger has dam 5d6 which means avg dam 18
  If the total damage is over 1200 it causes a bug, so please
  don't make any weapons more than avg dam around 100.

~

93 ITEM_AFFECTS_TABLE 'ITEM AFFECTS TABLE'~
`@i`$TEM `$AFFECTS`@-`$TABLE`@:``
  Modifies stats or hit/dam and such things.

  1 - strength             2 - dex
  3 - intelligence         4 - wisdom
  5 - constitution         6 - sex
  7 - class                8 - level *woohoo*
  9 - age                 12 - mana
 13 - hp                  14 - move
 15 - gold                16 - experience
 17 - ac                  18 - hit roll
 19 - dam roll            20 - saves
 21 - save vs rod         22 - save vs petrification
 23 - save vs breath      24 - save vs spell

  Command: set obj <obj> aff <number> <amount>
    Example: set obj holy aff 18 4
    A holy Avenger with +3 hitroll
~

93 AMMUNITION_TABLE 'AMMUNITION TABLE'~
Caliber	AmmType	D.Noun	Special	D.Type	Recoil	Vnums		Damage
=======	=======	======	=======	======	======	===========	======
9mm	FMJ	`7shot``	n/a	PIERCE	12	1800/1802	40-80
	JHP	`7shot``	FLECH.	PIERCE	12	1801/1803	50-100
.45ACP	FMJ	`8s`7h`&o`7t``	n/a	PIERCE	15	1804/1806	50-100
	JHP	`8s`7h`&o`7t``	FLECH.	PIERCE	15	1805/1807	62-125
.22	FMJ	shot	n/a	PIERCE	10	1808/1810	20-40
	JHP	shot	FLECH.	PIERCE	10	1809/1811	30-55

Recoil is measured in pulses. (12 = 1 round)
Damage values are base, and can be modified by gun skills and the gun itself(v3).
The vnums are used by the code. DO NOT EDIT THOSE LISTED HERE!
Some ammunition has special bits.
FLECH.	= AC damage reduction is more powerful against this round.
PENE.	= AC damage reduction is less powerful against this round.
WIDE	= Hinders victim's dodging, thus reducing the defense bonus from the dodge skill.
ETHEREAL= Hinders victim's phasing, thus reducing the defense bonus from the phase skill.
~

